Or you can email us.General FAQs​How can I be considered for a contribution, including grants and sponsorships, from Altria?​​Grant applications are distributed at the company's discretion. The Contributions staff continually scans for organizations and activities that best align with Altria's selected focus areas and outcomes. Invitations are only issued proactively. The company will not respond to unsolicited applications or requests. Learn MoreGeneral FAQsWhat is Altria's corporate structure?​​Altria is the parent company of various operating and service companies. Learn MoreGeneral FAQs​How can a minority supplier obtain business with Altria?​​In addition to the usual supplier selection channels, Altria and its companies maintain a minority and women-owned business list that is made available to appropriate personnel at the companies. Learn MoreGeneral FAQs​​How can I offer a product or service to Altria or its companies?​​To find out more about our companies and how to do business with us please visit the following webpages:

Altria and its companies' Supplier Diversity Development Process

How Altria works with its business partners General FAQsI'm a retailer and have a sales related question. Who should I contact?​​For retailer or wholesaler related questions, please call 800-343-0975 and select option 4 and then option 2.General FAQsWho can I contact about benefit related questions?​​For all benefit related questions, call the Altria Group Benefits Center at 1-800-872-3777. This includes active employees, former employees, retirees, spouses, domestic partners or beneficiaries of deceased employees.General FAQs​How do I obtain information on staffing and employment?​For staffing or employment related questions, visit our Employment WebsiteGeneral FAQsHow do I obtain information about the Direct Stock Purchase and Dividend Reinvestment Plan?​​Please visit the Shareholder Services section of this websiteInvestor FAQsWhere can I find information about tax basis for Philip Morris International or Kraft?​​For PMI, please review the attached document or PMI Canadian Tax. For Kraft, please review the attached document or Spin-Off Information.Investor FAQsWhere can I find a comprehensive list of Investor FAQs?​​To find a detailed list of general, acquisition and spin-off FAQs visit our Investors section.Investor FAQs

